Dear Mr. Muro,

I hope this message finds you well. I am following up on our correspondence
from February regarding the Koseki Tohon retrieval for my grandfather,
Masato Wayne Sumida (=E5=A2=A8=E7=94=B0 =E6=94=BF=E4=BA=BA).

I have two updates:

*1. Proof of Relationship =E2=80=94 Complete*

I now have the full chain of certified US vital records in hand:

   - My birth certificate (certified) =E2=80=94 names my father, Paul Morih=
iko
   Sumida
   - My father's birth certificate (certified) =E2=80=94 names his father, =
Masato
   Wayne Sumida
   - My grandfather's death certificate (certified) =E2=80=94 confirms his =
identity

This establishes the unbroken descent chain: Masato (Issei) =E2=86=92 Paul =
(Nisei)
=E2=86=92 Ryan (Sansei).

*2. A-File Received =E2=80=94 No Banchi Found*

The US National Archives has delivered my grandfather's complete Alien
Immigration Case File (A-File No. 4329588). Unfortunately, the file does
not contain a specific lot/house number (banchi) for the Etajima-mura
address.

However, the A-File does contain substantial identity information that may
assist with the municipal search:
Detail Source
Full name Wayne Masato Sumida (=E5=A2=A8=E7=94=B0 =E6=94=BF=E4=BA=BA)
Date of birth October 13, 1902 (one document says 1903)
Birthplace Hiroshima, Japan
Mother Listed as "Kite Sumida" at Akizukimura, Akigun, Hiroshimaken
Wife Hisako Sumida
Son Morihiko Sumida
Ship Atsuta Maru (NYK Line), arrived Seattle, August 1918
Alien Registration No. 4329588

Regarding the mother's name: in the original 1918 ship manifest (List or
Manifest of Alien Passengers, S.S. Atsuta Maru, sailing from Kobe, July 15,
1918), the nearest relative column for my grandfather's entry clearly
lists *"Mother,
Take Sumida, Etajima-mura, Akigun, Hiroshimaken."* The A-File's 1942
Application for Certificate of Identification lists "Kite Sumida" as his
mother. It is possible that "Kite" or "Kito" was a stepmother, or that the
name was recorded differently due to handwriting. I wanted to bring both
names to your attention in case it helps narrow the search.

*My question:* Given that the A-File did not produce a banchi, but we now
have the complete proof of relationship chain and the additional identity
details above, is it possible to proceed with the Koseki retrieval from
Kure City (formerly Etajima-mura)? I understand from your earlier message
that some municipal offices have accepted applications without the lot
number.

I am ready to send you the certified documents and the A-File whenever you
are prepared to proceed. Please let me know if there is any other
information I can provide.

Thank you for your patience and continued guidance.

Best regards,

Ryan Masato Sumida

